there%20was%20an%20extremely%20high%20turnover%20rate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20overworked%2C%20underpaid%20without%20training%2C%20and%20expected%20to%20wear%20many%20hats.%20They%20micromanaged%2C%20and%20taking%20paid-time%20off%20was%20always%20an%20issue%20due%20to%20understaffing.%C2%A0%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20excited%20about%20my%20old%20job%2C%20since%20it%20was%20my%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college.%20But%20just%20three%20months%20in%2C%20project%20managers%20were%20leaving%2C%20and%20I%20was%20left%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20had%20an%20overabundance%20of%20clients%20while%20understaffed%2C%20so%20we%20were%20all%20overworked.%20I%20had%20to%20take%20on%20many%20responsibilities%20I%20wasn't%20compensated%20for%20and%20worked%20simultaneously%20with%20at%20least%2012%20or%2013%20clients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20constantly%20working%20overtime%20at%20my%20last%20job%2C%20which%20was%20so%20taxing%20to%20my%20mental%20health%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20miserable.%20I%20put%20in%20so%20much%20effort%2C%20but%20there%20weren't%20clear%20delineations%20of%20growth%20opportunities.%20When%20I%20asked%20for%20a%20raise%2C%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20do%20enough.%26quot%3B%20I%20left%20that%20conversation%20feeling%20expendable%20and%20questioned%20why%20I%20was%20staying%20when%20I%20was%20unhappy%2C%20poorly%20compensated%20for%20the%20workload%2C%20and%20without%20proper%20guidance%20or%20training.%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20other%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20editing%20LinkedIn%20to%20say%20I%20was%20open%20to%20other%20positions%2C%20a%20recruiter%20from%20my%20current%20job%20reached%20out.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20hesitant%20because%20they%20scouted%20me%20out%20of%20the%20blue.%20But%20after%20learning%20more%20about%20the%20position%2C%20I%20saw%20they%20had%20all%20the%20benefits%20my%20current%20job%20was%20missing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20previous%20jo