%20US%20power.%20Xi%20has%20largely%20avoided%20criticism%20of%20Russia's%20actions%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20China%20has%20been%20a%20crucial%20trading%20partner%20to%20Russia%20after%20it%20was%20cut%20off%20by%20the%20West.%20China%20has%20even%20been%20sending%20the%20Kremlin%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-sending-russia-masses-of-military-gear-including-drones-report-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenough%20military%20equipment%20for%20an%20entire%20army%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fchina-firms-russia-body-armor-bullet-proof-drones-thermal-optics-army-equipment-shanghai-h-win%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPolitico%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sergey%20Radchenko%2C%20a%20Cold%20War%20historian%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20op-ed%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F23%2Fopinion%2Fchina-russia-us-cold-war.html%3Fcampaign_id%3D9%26emc%3Dedit_nn_20230725%26instance_id%3D98372%26nl%3Dthe-morning%26regi_id%3D185532493%26segment_id%3D140198%26te%3D1%26user_id%3De3919ac9df4950f24160d87edcafd546%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it's%20unwise%20for%20Putin%20to%20put%20all%20his%20eggs%20in%20one%20China-sized%20basket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party's%20approach%20to%20geopolitics%20is%20rooted%20in%20an%20ancient%20strategic%20culture%20of%20playing%20other%20nations%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20dismissed%20as%20barbarians%20during%20China's%20imperial%20times%20%E2%80%94%20against%20one%20another%20for%20China's%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20Radchenko%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20China's%20actions%20in%20the%20early%201970s%2C%20when%20Chinese%20leader%20Mao%20Zedong%20cozied%20up%20to%20the%20US%2C%20his%20%26quot%3Bavowed%20foe%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20his%20country%20was%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20war%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20A%20senior%20Chinese%20official%20in%201975%20said%20the%20move%20wasn't%20because%20China%20had%20%26quot%3Bgood%20feelings%20toward%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20but%20was%20intended%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20US%20conflict%20with%20the%20Soviets.%20But%2C%20Radchenko%20said%2C%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade%20China%20was%20playing%20the%20US%20against%20the%20USSR%2C%20and%20had%20grown%20closer%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20remains%20the%20same%20secretive%2C%20self-serving%20Communist%20Party%20state%20that%20it%20was%20in%20Mao's%20day%2C%20with%20an%20outlook%20on%20global%20politics%20in%20which%20alignments%20are%20viewed%20as%20temporary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadchenko%20noted%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Frussia-economy-china-vassal-war-ukraine-western-sanctions-2023-5%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20has%20become%20increasingly%20reliant%20on%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20support%2C%20adding%20that%20Putin%20%26quot%3Bhas%20made%20a%20potentially%20grave%20error%2C%20burning%20bridges%20with%20the%20West%20to%20go%20all%20in%20with%20China%20in%20reckless%20disregard%20for%20Beijing's%20track%20record%20of%20instrumentalizing%20its%20friendships.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20argued%20that%2C%20at%20least%20for%20now%2C%20China%20may%20need%20Russia%20too.%20Jonathan%20Ward%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Atlas%20Group%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinside