piracy%20is%20unlikely%20to%20ever%20be%20entirely%20eradicated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20ships%20go%20to%20sea%2C%20there's%20gonna%20be%20piracy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'wild%2C%20wild%20West'%20on%20the%20open%20seas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcKnight%2C%20who%20oversaw%20Combined%20Task%20Force%20151%20for%20five%20months%20in%202009%2C%20said%20the%20multinational%20counter-piracy%20task%20force%20was%20created%20to%20address%20the%20increasing%20issue%20of%20maritime%20piracy%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Somalia%20that%20exploded%20in%20the%20mid-to-late%20aughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20%26quot%3Bpirates%26quot%3B%20would%20capture%20vessels%20in%20international%20waters%20and%20bring%20them%20back%20into%20territorial%20waters%20%E2%80%94%20the%20seas%20up%20to%2012%20miles%20surrounding%20a%20sovereign%20state%20in%20which%20no%20other%20authorities%20have%20jurisdiction%20%E2%80%94%20to%20avoid%20being%20apprehended%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%2C%20located%20between%20Yemen%20to%20the%20north%20and%20Somalia%20to%20the%20south%2C%20became%20a%20prime%20piracy%20spot%20amid%20the%20surge%20thanks%20to%20its%20status%20as%20a%20massive%20trade%20route%20that%20sees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20081204080826%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fnews.yahoo.com%2Fs%2Fap%2F20081202%2Fap_on_re_af%2Fpiracy%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%2C000%20merchant%20ships%3C%2Fa%3E%20pass%20through%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228660%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c05fb2671ed600191529b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225773%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20of%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20wild%2C%20wild%20West%20out%20there.%20There%20are%20hundreds%20of%20dhows%20either%20smuggling%20arms%2C%20drugs%2C%20or%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20McKnight%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20narrow%20ships%20that%20often%20operate%20without%20an%20identification%20signal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERampant%20drug%20trafficking%20throughout%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%20has%20spawned%20a%20biting%20nickname%20for%20the%20waterway%20%E2%80%94%20the%20hash%20highway%20%E2%80%94%20and%20weapons%20are%20often%20carried%20from%20Africa%20to%20Yemen%20on%20its%20seas%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20trying%20to%20pick%20a%20needle%20out%20of%20a%20haystack%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20apprehending%20traffickers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoarding%20parties%20can%20bring%20danger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20intercepting%20illegal%20goods%20on%20the%20open%20ocean%20is%20a%20laborious%20one%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiting%20his%20own%20experience%20commanding%20the%20still%20operational%20anti-piracy%20task%20force%2C%20McKnight%20said%20officials%20will%20usually%20go%20after%20a%20vessel%20only%20after%20they%20have%20sufficient%20intelligence%20suggesting%20the%20ship%20is%20carrying%20illegal%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20they%20watch%20and%20wait.%20Authorities%20will%20track%20these%20dhows%2C%20sometimes%20for%20days%2C%20McKnight%20said%2C%20as%20they%20hug%20the%20coastline.%20But%20the%20moment%20they%20exit%20territorial%20waters%20and%20make%20for%20the%20open%20seas%2C%20maritime%20officials%20are%20ready%20to%20apprehend%20them%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Naval%20search%20and%20seizure%20team%20from%20the%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Anzio%20and%20U.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20Maritime%20Safety%20and%20Security%20Team%2091104%20dispose%20of%20bags%20of%20illegal%20narcotics%20aboard%20a%20drug%20smuggling%20vessel%20October%2015%2C%202009%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c050f61f17bb00196e1ca4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Naval%20search%20and%20seizure%20team%20from%20the%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Anzio%20and%20U.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20Maritime%20Safety%20and%20Security%20Team%2091104%20dispose%20of%20bags%20of%20illegal%20narcotics%20aboard%20a%20drug%20smuggling%20vessel%20October%2015%2C%202009%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Matthew%20Bash%2FU.S.%20Navy%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20comes%20the%20boarding%20party%2C%20McKnight%20said.%20Officials%20deal%20with%20both%20compliant%20and%20non-compliant%20boardings%20depending%20on%20whether%20the%20vessel's%20inhabitants%20agree%20to%20be%20boarded.%20Only%20Naval%20Special%20Warfare%20forces%20can%20conduct%20a%20non-compliant%20boarding%2C%20given%20the%20dangerous%20nature%20of%20the%20interaction%2C%20McKnight%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20compliant%20boardings%20carry%20real%20risk%20though%3B%20a%20stray%20seaman%20could%20always%20be%20waiting%20below%20deck%2C%20ready%20to%20pounce%2C%20McKnight%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20for%20the%20faint%20of%20heart%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20people%20on%20these%20dhows%20are%20simply%20hired%20to%20transport%20the%20goods%2C%20McKnight%20said.%20Sometimes%20they%20know%20what%20they're%20carrying%2C%20other%20times%2C%20they're%20unaware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20care%20what%20they%20are%20transporting%2C%20could%20be%20rugs%2C%20drugs%2C%20or%20guns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20maritime%20officials%20do%20encounter%20a%20%26quot%3Bjackpot%26quot%3B%20like%20the%20weapons%20seizure%20documented%20in%20this%20month's%20Navy%20court%20documents%2C%20government%20leaders%20can't%20help%20but%20show%20off%20their%20treasu