rom%20their%20English%20medium%20school%20and%20enrol%20them%20in%20a%20government-run%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20Shashi%20washed%20tourists%E2%80%99%20clothes%20until%202008%20when%20she%20had%20a%20visitor%20from%20Ireland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20told%20us%20that%20he%20admires%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F311742%2Fgujarat-woman-chef-fought-stereotypes-to-start-secret-kitchen-restaurant-australia-aanal-kotak%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20lot.%20And%20since%20he%20was%20our%20guest%2C%20I%20thought%20of%20offering%20him%20the%20food%20we%20had.%20I%20did%20not%20have%20sufficient%20means%2C%20so%20I%20could%20only%20serve%20him%20%3Cem%3Eroti%20sabzi%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20he%20said%20it%20was%20delicious.%20He%20was%20in%20Udaipur%20for%20four%20to%20five%20days%20and%20he%20visited%20us%20each%20day.%20I%20would%20cook%20various%20vegetables%20for%20him%20and%20he%20relished%20them%20all.%20He%20even%20wanted%20to%20learn%20how%20the%20food%20was%20cooked%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20gave%20her%20the%20idea%20to%20start%20cooking%20classes%20for%20tourists%20and%20%E2%80%98Shashi%20Cooking%20Classes%E2%80%99%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHer%20%E2%80%98English%20Vinglish%E2%80%99%20Moment%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20her%20initial%20experience%20of%20setting%20up%20the%20class%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20did%20not%20have%20a%20good%20kitchen.%20We%20just%20had%20a%20small%20wooden%20table.%20Our%20first%20guest%20was%20an%20Australian%20couple.%20I%20was%20so%20nervous%2C%20my%20hands%20were%20shaking%20and%20I%20was%20also%20sweating.%20I%20even%20dropped%20a%20teacup%2C%20but%20they%20encouraged%20me%20by%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20okay%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%