e%20credit%3A%20Portia%20Putatunda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20started%20her%20boarding%20school%20with%20three%20children%20and%20the%20number%20has%20grown%20to%2010%20presently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20herself%20%E2%80%9Cmother%E2%80%9D%20to%20those%20children%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20children%20are%20not%20orphans%20and%20are%20not%20abandoned%20by%20choice%20but%20by%20poverty.%20Around%2050%20percent%20of%20these%20kids%20do%20not%20have%20a%20surviving%20parent%2C%20but%20the%20rest%20have%20parents%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20raise%20them.%20This%20is%20where%20I%20come%20in%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20children%20keep%20me%20going%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20morning%20Portia%20wakes%20up%20to%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20children%20outside%20her%20window.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20would%20call%20me%20Portia%20madam%20and%20giggle%20at%20my%20window.%20I%20believe%20this%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20wake%20up%20every%20morning.%20After%20waking%20up%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20I%20do%20is%20to%20light%20up%20the%20tandoor%20to%20heat%20up%20the%20classrooms%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20use%20firewood%20or%20cow%20dung%20for%20the%20tandoor%20and%20I%20cook%20on%20top%20of%20that%20sometimes.%20I%20prepare%20breakfast%20and%20the%20kids%20get%20ready%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20children%20start%20their%20day%20with%20a%20small%20assembly%20and%20then%20head%20to%20their%20classes.%20%E2%80%9CI%20teach%20them%20everything%20from%20mathematics%20and%20science%20to%20English%20and%20art.%20I%20also%20conduct%20many%20activities%20like%20gardening%2C%20dancing%2C%20etc%20throughout%20the%20week%20to%20keep%20the%20learning%20wholesome%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20children%E2%80%99s%20age%20group%20is%20between%20three%20and%2010%20years%20old.%20The