th%20Acharya%20Jagadish%20Chandra%20Bose%2C%20philosopher%20Brajendra%20Nath%20Seal%2C%20social%20reformer%20Sivanath%20Sastri%2C%20political%20figure%20Surendranath%20Banerjee%2C%20and%20historian%20Acharya%20Prafulla%20Chandra%20Ray.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20requested%20the%20then%20Viceroy%20of%20India%20Lord%20Curzon%20that%20Bandyopadhyay%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F28236%2Findian-scientist-discovery-in-ending-malaria%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eawarded%20for%20his%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Viceroy%20obliged.%20In%201903%2C%20Bandyopadhyay%20was%20awarded%20King%20Edward%20VII%E2%80%99s%20Gold%20Medal%20and%20felicitated%20at%20the%20University%20Senate%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201918%2C%20when%20a%20malaria%20epidemic%20struck%20the%20country%2C%20Dr%20Gopal%20Chandra%20Chattopadhyay%20started%20a%20public%20health%20movement%20to%20control%20the%20spread%2C%20and%20Bandyopadhyay%20joined%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20began%20educating%20the%20villagers%20about%20sanitisation%20and%20good%20hygienic%20practices.%20The%20Anti-Malaria%20Cooperative%20Society%20was%20founded%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20the%20village%20level%20in%20India%20at%20Panihati%20on%2024%20March%201918.%20Bandopadhyay%20was%20the%20secretary%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F316087%2Fassam-couple-helps-rural-northeast-india-access-affordable-mental-healthcare-mita%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20helm%20of%20activities%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20encouraged%20cleaning%20ponds%20and%20drains%20in%20the%20village%2C%20clearing%20the%20garbage%20that%20choked%20the%20lakes%20and%20distributing%20mosquito%20nets.%20This%20compelled%20other%20villages%20to%20start%20similar%20associations%20to%20curb%20the%20spread%20of%20malaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotable%20author%20Amitav%20Ghosh%